# MoodLab full-stack mobile

## Product

MoodLab is a **creator-first LUT photo editor** — not a text journal. Core loop: import → mood/LUT → beauty → text → export.

Product docs: `docs/product/`. Architecture: `docs/architecture/`. UI: `docs/design/`.

## Monorepo

- **pnpm workspaces** — install from repo root
- **Shared types** — `EditRecipe`, `LutDefinition`, `BeautySettings` in `@moodlab/shared`
- **LUT parser** — `@moodlab/lut-engine` for `.cube` files
- **Mobile** — `@moodlab/mobile` (Expo Router)
- **API** — `@moodlab/api` (catalog + projects; Postgres later)

## Mobile (Expo)

- Routes under `apps/mobile/app/` — editor is `editor.tsx` (stack, not tab)
- API via `apps/mobile/lib/api.ts`
- JS LUT preview: `apps/mobile/lib/render-preview.ts` — native RenderCore replaces this
- Dark theme tokens: `apps/mobile/constants/theme.ts`
- Run `pnpm --filter @moodlab/mobile typecheck` after TS changes

## API (Hono)

- REST under `/api/v1/` — packs, luts, manifest, projects
- Catalog loaders in `apps/api/src/catalog.ts`
- JSON: `{ data }` or `{ error }`
- Do not add image processing endpoints for normal LUT edits

## LUT assets

- Metadata: `data/lut_catalog.json`
- Files: `luts/original/*.cube`
- Regenerate: `python3 tools/generate_original_luts.py`

## Testing

- Vitest in `packages/shared`, `packages/lut-engine`, `apps/api`
- Mobile: Jest/RTL or Maestro when features stabilize
